From 6e5cb88a9786e13849339c3d778d60d552e3b59d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 23:17:41 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 8/9] libavfilter: add libvmaf_tune filter (SCAFFOLD; vmaf-tune
 helper)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

New 2-input video filter that runs alongside a 1-pass encode and emits
a recommended CRF for the next pass:

    ffmpeg -i in.mp4 -i ref.mp4 -lavfi '[0:v][1:v]libvmaf_tune' -f null -
    [Parsed_libvmaf_tune_0 @ 0x...] recommended_crf=23.4 (target_vmaf=95.0, n_frames=240)

AVOptions: model, feature, n_threads, recommend_target_vmaf (95),
recommend_crf_min (18), recommend_crf_max (51), recommend_passes (1).

SCAFFOLD per ADR-0312:
  * Filter skeleton, AVOption table, init/uninit, frame pass-through
    on the main pad with framesync ref-pad accepted.
  * CRF recommendation is a thin linear interpolation between
    crf_min and crf_max around the target_vmaf — the full Optuna TPE
    recommend loop stays in tools/vmaf-tune (recommend.py).
  * Side-data emission and full libvmaf scoring deferred to a
    follow-up patch (see ADR-0312 Alternatives).

ADR: docs/adr/0312-ffmpeg-patches-vmaf-tune-integration.md
---
